30:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>On the other side of the cost spectrum, <a href=\"http://www.pervices.com/\">pervices</a>\nmakes some really high-throughput, PCIe devices for when you need to log all\nthe traffic ever. The software and community support for this is less good,\nthough (for which you can blame @outofculture).</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>You can also browse through the <a href=\"https://gnuradio.org/redmine/projects/gnuradio/wiki/Hardware\">big\nlist</a> of all\ncompatible hardware.</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","categoryHTML":"<h2>SDR (Software Defined Radio)</h2><h3>Hardware</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Antennas are their own body of options and tradeoffs, about which I know\nnothing.</li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:30:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","categoryHTML":"<h2>Amateur Radio (a.k.a Ham Radio)</h2><h3>Links</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.project25.org/\">Project 25</a></li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:17:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","categoryHTML":"<h2>Amateur Radio (a.k.a Ham Radio)</h2><h3>Links</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Project_25\">Project 25 wikipedia</a></li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:17:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kyleterry/awesome-radio","categoryHTML":"<h2>Amateur Radio (a.k.a Ham Radio)</h2><h3>Links</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trunked_radio_system\">Trunked Radio wikipedia</a></li>","updatedAt":"2014-12-19T06:17:26.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1418947200000,"to":1419033599999,"previousId":"2014-12-20","nextId":"2014-12-18","nextName":"Dec 18th, 2014","previousName":"Dec 2